/i> ‘to defend’ + <i>anēr</i> ‘man, warrior’ (genitive <i>andros</i>). The name became extremely popular in the post-classical period, and was borne by several individuals in the New Testament and some early Christian saints. Its use as a common given name throughout Europe, however, derives largely from the fame of  Alexander the Great , King of Macedon (  356–323  bc  ), around whom a large body of popular legend grew up in late antiquity, much of which came to be embodied in the medieval ‘Alexander romances’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":59,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Alica Bardolf was born about 1156, in Kingston Russell, Dorset, England. She married Odo de Russell before 1180, in Strensham, Worcestershire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 13 November 1223, in England, at the age of 68."},"et":{"about 1156–13 November 1223":"umbes 1156–13. november 1223","1150–1230":"1150–1230","1180–1224":"1180–1224","1156–1223":"1156–1223","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","about 1180":"umbes 1180","1223":"1223","1156":"1156","1230":"1230","about 1156":"umbes 1156","1150":"1150","13 November 1223":"13. november 1223","before 1180":"enne 1180","1180":"1180","Strensham, Worcestershire, England":"Strensham, Worcestershire, England","England":"England","Kingston Russell, Dorset, England":"Kingston Russell, Dorset, England","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England"},"fi":{"about 1156–13 November 1223":"noi